 width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/sam-fender-liam-payne@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sam-fender">Sam Fender</a> has reflected on the death of ex- <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/one-direction">One Direction</a> singer <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/liam-payne">Liam Payne</a> last year – see what he had to say below.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/liam-payne-one-direction-obituary-3803755">Liam Payne 1993-2024: One Direction star who helped spark a pop phenomenon</a></strong></li></ul><p> Speaking to <a href="https://www.thetimes.com/article/2477ea71-a04f-46ee-980e-f2a6dad38df6?shareToken=db88db7b003ab51d0c2f12a93295de6f" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Sunday Times</em></a> about his latest album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sam-fender-people-watching-review-3840019">&#39;People Watching&#39;</a> , Sam Fender broke down the themes of several tracks on the record. One of those tracks is &#39;TV Dinner&#39;, which has been lauded since its release as a takedown of the music industry.</p><p> On the track, Fender mentions the late <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/amy-winehouse">Amy Winehouse</a> and the industry&#39;s treatment of her leading up to her <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/amy-winehouse-180-1280292#:~:text=Amy%20Winehouse%20died%20today%20(July,were%20unable%20to%20revive%20her.">untimely death in 2011</a> : “ <em>Like Winehouse, she was just a bairn / They love her now but bled her then</em> “. The same thing tragically happened to Liam Payne, who suffered a <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/one-directions-liam-payne-had-died-aged-31-3803523">fatal fall from a third-floor balcony at the CasaSur Palermo Hotel in Buenos Aires, Argentina</a> last year. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Sam Fender - TV Dinner (Official Lyric Video)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6znfm2sjlmE?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Prior to Payne&#39;s death, the artist was largely criticised by the public just days before the tragic fall as he had <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/niall-horan-recalls-final-goodbye-with-brother-liam-payne-days-before-death-3804102">attended ex-bandmate Niall Horan&#39;s Argentina concert</a> and was mocked for “stealing” the attention of fans who had paid to see Horan. Payne had also had several public battles with addiction, in<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-payne-rehab-stay-viral-one-direction-comments-3467296">July 2023 opening up about a recent stint in rehab</a> .</p><p> Reflecting on Payne&#39;s passing, Sam Fender revealed to <em>The Sunday Times</em> that he had written &#39;TV Dinner&#39; shortly before the tragic incident: “It&#39;s the British culture of building them up to knock &#39;em down.这是狂野的。 I wrote that, then Liam Payne died.” </p><figure id="attachment_3829687" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3829687" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3829687" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images.jpg" alt="Liam Payne" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Liam-Payne-Photo-by-Slaven-Vlasic_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3829687" class="wp-caption-text"> Liam Payne – CREDIT: Slaven Vlasic/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> Fender went on to add that he thought Payne was let down by the industry: “You think of the amount of times he was getting dragged through the press and he didn&#39;t help himself, did he?祝福他。我记得看过他在里面的一些视频，就像是“上帝，真是个山雀”。 But the reality was that he was just a young lad, famous far too young, who had addiction trouble — and everyone hit him with the pitchforks.”</p><p> Sam Fender&#39;s comments echo that of <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-darkness">The Darkness</a> &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/justin-hawkins">Justin Hawkins</a> who had previously criticised Payne but <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-darkness-justin-hawkins-defends-criticising-liam-payne-interview-3820812">explained why he isn&#39;t going to remove his posts in light of the singer&#39;s death</a> .</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sam-fender-people-watching-review-3840019">Sam Fender  - “观看人”评论：反光和敏锐的独立摇滚乐</a></strong></li></ul><p>Back in March 2023, Hawkins shared a video in which he looked at previous interviews that Payne had done, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4BCj0nTEnE0" target="_blank" rel="noopener">criticised some of his behaviour as coming across as “arrogant”</a> . A large segment of the video centred around the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-payne-tells-logan-paul-one-direction-member-threw-me-up-a-wall-3239096">divisive discussion Payne had with Logan Paul</a> , in which he recalled the formation of One Direction and implied that he was meant to be seen as the main member in the line-up.</p><p> Although Hawkins seemed to defend Payne to an extent – describing him as his “favourite” member and sympathising with him as one whose brand “suffered the most post-One Direction” – the comments made were brought to light once again following the singer&#39;s death.</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-darkness-justin-hawkins-defends-criticising-liam-payne-interview-3820812">He said</a> : “It&#39;s really sad what happened to him, but at the end of the day, it&#39;s not going to change my view on those specific behaviours. Everybody&#39;s complex and there are layers to this and laughing at some stuff that&#39;s laughable… that&#39;s what I do. It&#39;s what I&#39;ll always do.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Sam Fender reacts to &#039;Seventeen Going Under&#039; being named NME&#039;s Album Of The Year 2021" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/DOiTh1M6Uhc?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sam-fender-people-watching-review-3840019">four-star review of &#39;People Watching&#39;</a> , Tilly Foulkes wrote for <em>NME</em> : “Reflective, analytical and vulnerable, &#39;People Watching&#39; does exactly what the title may suggest: takes stock of the characters, friends and loved ones who have made Fender the person he is today. He approaches each track with sensitivity as he looks back on his life so far – perhaps even with an inkling of guilt – and contemplates who he may be next.”</p><p>同时，Fender最近<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-planning-next-album-ive-got-a-load-of-new-songs-already-3839928">透露，他已经在进行后续行动</a>，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-more-huge-uk-outdoor-shows-for-summer-2025-3837652">宣布了</a>夏季即将在夏季<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-huge-summer-2025-uk-stadium-shows-buy-tickets-3814931">即将举行的英国体育场巡回演出</a>的日期，包括8月16日在曼彻斯特的Wythenshawe Park，8月22日，爱丁堡的夏季会议和Boucher Road Players在贝尔法斯特作为8月28日至关重要系列的一部分。 </p><figure id="attachment_3839939" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3839939" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3839939" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing.jpg" alt="Sam Fender performs on Day 2 of Leeds Festival 2023 at Bramham Park on August 26, 2023 in Leeds, England. (Photo by Matthew Baker/Getty Images)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Sam-Fender-performing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3839939" class="wp-caption-text"> Sam Fender performs on Day 2 of Leeds Festival 2023 at Bramham Park on August 26, 2023 in Leeds, England. (Photo by Matthew Baker/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p>对前两个节目的支持将来自<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/olivia-dean">奥利维亚·迪恩（Olivia Dean）</a> ，而<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/cmat">CMAT</a>将在贝尔法斯特（Belfast）开幕。 <a href="https://ticketmaster-uk.tm7559.net/c/2862475/431519/7559?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.co.uk%2Fsam-fender-tickets%2Fartist%2F5242347" target="_blank" rel="noopener">请访问此处购买门票</a>，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-more-huge-uk-outdoor-shows-for-summer-2025-3837652">在此处</a>找到英国巡回演出的清单。</p><p>这位歌手兼作曲家最近也被宣布为2025年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announced-as-record-store-day-uk-official-ambassador-3834386">唱片商店Day</a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announced-as-record-store-day-uk-official-ambassador-3834386">的正式大使</a>（定于4月12日），并将发行两首新歌曲，作为庆祝活动的特别EP的一部分。在下个月的仪式上，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brit-awards-2025-nominees-3831514">获得了两个英国奖项的提名</a>：年度艺术家和Alt/Rock Act。</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-on-liam-payne-he-was-just-a-young-lad-famous-far-too-young-who-had-addiction-trouble-and-everyone-hit-him-with-the-pitchforks-3840603">Sam Fender on Liam Payne: “He was just a young lad, famous far too young, who had addiction trouble — and everyone hit him with the pitchforks”</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 “Mastermind” in Pop Smoke's killing sentenced to 29 years in prison https://www.nme.com/news/music/mastermind-in-pop-smokes-killing-sentenced-to-29-years-in-prison-3840589?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=mastermind-in-pop-smokes-killing-sentenced-to-29-years-in-prisonSurej Singh Mon, 24 Feb 2025 02:08:32 +0000 Music NewsNewsRap https://www.nme.com/?p=3840589 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Corey Walker was one of four people charged in connection with fatally shooting the rapper in 2020</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mastermind-in-pop-smokes-killing-sentenced-to-29-years-in-prison-3840589">“Mastermind” in Pop Smoke&#39;s killing sentenced to 29 years in prison</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/pop-smoke@2000x1270-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> One of four people charged in connection to rapper <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/pop-smoke">Pop Smoke</a> &#39;s murder in 2020 has been sentenced to 29 years in prison.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/pop-smoke-shoot-for-the-stars-aim-for-the-moon-album-review-2701075">Pop Smoke – &#39;Shoot For The Stars, Aim For The Moon&#39; review: Brooklyn rapper&#39;s posthumous debut matches rising star&#39;s ambition</a></strong></li></ul><p> Pop Smoke – real name Bashar Jackson – was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pop-smoke-has-been-killed-age-20-reports-2611746">killed in a rented Hollywood Hills home during a home-invasion robbery in February 2020</a> .他今年20岁。 The group allegedly invaded the rapper&#39;s Airbnb rental in Los Angeles with the aim of stealing his diamond-studded Rolex watch and Cuban link chain. They ended up stealing the watch, which they are alleged to have resold for $2,000 (£1,405).</p><p> On Friday (February 21), 24-year-old Corey Walker was sentenced to 29 years in prison at a courtroom in Los Angeles. The sentencing came two weeks after Walker <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pop-smoke-murder-suspect-faces-29-years-in-prison-after-accepting-plea-deal-3835227">pleaded guilty to voluntary manslaughter and home invasion robbery with gun and gang enhancements at a hearing earlier this month</a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3835233" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3835233" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3835233" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270.jpg" alt="Pop Smoke" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025_popsmoke_getty_2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3835233" class="wp-caption-text"> Pop Smoke performs at the Soulfrito Music Festival at Barclays Center on August 30, 2019 in New York CREDIT: Arik Mazur/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> According to a <a href="https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/pop-smoke-killer-apologizes-sentenced-rapper-death-1235275399/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Rolling Stone</em></a> report, Walker appeared “deeply remorseful” at the sentencing and offered an apology to the family of the late rapper: “Even though the Jackson family isn&#39;t here in court today, I would like to sincerely apologise for my unforgivable actions, although there&#39;s no apology that amounts to the taking of someone&#39;s life. I would also like to take this opportunity to apologise to my family for the pain and embarrassment that they have endured over the last five years, as well as an apology to my community.”</p><p> Walker – who initially faced a life sentence before accepting a plea deal that would reduce his charges to voluntary manslaughter for 29 years in prison – has also said he “takes responsibility” for his role in the crimes.</p><p> As for the three other people involved in the shooting and break in, a 19-year-old (who was 15 at the time) <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/18-year-old-confesses-fatally-shooting-pop-smoke-3442928">in 2023 admitted to fatally shooting Pop Smoke</a> . He will remain in a juvenile detention center until he&#39;s 25.</p><p> Another <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/man-pleads-guilty-to-voluntary-manslaughter-of-pop-smoke-3427423">pleaded guilty to voluntary manslaughter in April 2023</a> . As he was a 17 at the time of the 2020 shooting, the man also faced juvenile court in Inglewood, and was sentenced to four years and two months in a juvenile facility. </p><figure id="attachment_2996710" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2996710" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-2996710" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1.jpg" alt="Pop Smoke" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pop-smoke-2020-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2996710" class="wp-caption-text"> Pop Smoke CREDIT: Johnny Nunez/WireImage</figcaption></figure><p> The final person involved in the shooting, Keandre Rodgers – 18 at the time of the incident – was initially charged with murder, though his case is now being reassessed.</p><p> Speaking to <a href="https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/pop-smoke-killer-apologizes-sentenced-rapper-death-1235275399/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Rolling Stone</em></a> following the sentencing on Friday, Deputy District Attorney Hilary Williams said of Walker: “Corey Walker was not an innocent participant in any of this. He was the mastermind ringleader in the planning, driving and provision of weapons to minors. He did surveillance on the home earlier that night and exchanged or traded cars so that the vehicle he drove up in was now a four-door vehicle that could accommodate more individuals that could enter that home and violate the rights of Mr. Jackson and his friends 。 Mr. Walker knew exactly what he was doing.”</p><p> There was an outpouring of tributes from the hip-hop community following Jackson&#39;s death, with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/joey-bada">Joey Bada$$</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/pusha-t">Pusha T</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/50-cent">50 Cent</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/fivio-foreign">Fivio Foreign</a> and more paying their respects. Jackson&#39;s debut album, <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/pop-smoke-shoot-for-the-stars-aim-for-the-moon-album-review-2701075">&#39;Shoot for the Stars, Aim for the Moon&#39;</a> , was released posthumously in 2020. A second posthumous album, <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/pop-smoke-faith-review-2996952">&#39;Faith&#39;</a> , arrived the following year, featuring appearances from <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/rick-ross">Rick Ross</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/21-savage">21 Savage</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/takeoff">Takeoff</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/future">Future</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/dua-lipa">Dua Lipa</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/pharrell-williams">Pharrell</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kid-cudi">Kid Cudi</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/quavo">Quavo</a> and more.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mastermind-in-pop-smokes-killing-sentenced-to-29-years-in-prison-3840589">“Mastermind” in Pop Smoke&#39;s killing sentenced to 29 years in prison</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
